05308nam a22006495i 9780271022758DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20212003pau    fo  d z      eng d  a97802710227587 a10.1515/97802710227582doi  a(DE-B1597)583731  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  apaucUS-PA 4aD842b.K25 2004eb 7aHIS0360602bisacsh04a943.087/42221 aKahn, Arthur D., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aExperiment in Occupation :bWitness to the Turnabout: Anti-Nazi War to Cold War, 1944-1946 /cArthur D. Kahn. 1aUniversity Park, PA : bPenn State University Press, c[2021] 4cÂ©2003  a1 online resource (248 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tAbbreviations -- tIntroduction: An OSS Recruit Despite Himself -- tPART I : WHY WE FIGHT! -- t1 Soviet Partisans and Soviet Suspicions summer 1944 -- t2 ''We Do Not Call Upon the Germans to Revolt'' fall 1944 -- t3 The Capture-Liberation of Metz -- t4 The Battle of the Bulge winter 1944-1945 -- t5 Mainz: Investigating a Pre-VE Day Military Government spring 1945 -- t6 Interrogating Victims of Nazism and Nazis -- t7 Wuerzburg: Another Military Government Experience -- t8 ''What We Russians Like to Consider as a Typical American'' -- tPART II: POLICY CLASH IN MILITARY GOVERNMENT -- t9 ''Crack Patton's Military Government Wide Open!'' summer 1945 -- t10 ''If Only You Americans Weren't Here . . . !'' -- t11 Patton's Last Stand -- t12 Elections, the American Cure-All fall 1945 -- t13 Rehearsal for McCarthyism -- tPART III: TRIUMPH OF THE COLD WARRIORS -- t14 A Military Government in Crisis winter 1945-1946 -- t15 Elections: The American Panacea II -- t16 Democracy, American Zone Style! -- t17 Summing Up and the Collective Guilt Issue spring 1946 -- t18 Demoralized GIs -- tEpilogue: 1946-1947 -- tAppendices -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAs a participant in many of the events he writes about in Experiment in Occupation, Arthur Kahn offers a richly detailed account of the process by which the fight against Nazism came to be transformed into the Cold War. His story reveals how those in the Military Government of Germany who were dedicated to carrying out the war aims promulgated by Roosevelt and Eisenhower for a thorough democratization of Germany were ultimately defeated in their confrontation with powerful elements in the Military Government and in Washington who were more intent upon launching a preemptive war against the Soviet Union than upon the eradication of Nazism and German militarism. A twenty-three-year-old OSS operative, Arthur Kahn was assigned after D-Day to a psychological warfare unit, where at first he supervised prisoner-of-war interrogations and then served as an editor of intelligence. Instructed to respond to requests from Supreme Headquarters, he drafted proposals for psychological warfare approaches to critical situations at the front only to discover that a SHAEF directive banned calls to the Germans to revolt. Subsequently Kahn served in liaison with the Soviets and during the Battle of the Bulge at Montgomery's British headquarters. For several months before and after VE Day he traveled through the American Zone as an intelligence investigator and wrote a report that led to the dismissal of General George S. Patton as Military Governor of Bavaria. Appointed Chief Editor of Intelligence of the Information Control Division, he produced the most influential intelligence weekly in the American Zone. Kahn's portrayal of events in postwar Germany provides warnings for current and future American experiments in foreign occupation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCold War. 0aMilitary governmentzGermany. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945vPersonal narratives, American. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271022758423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780271022758.jpg  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK